parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple critical systems to malfunction, including the radio and headlights, which can lead to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Radio stops working
headlights fail to turn on
multiple electrical accessories malfunction simultaneously.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, posing a significant risk to the safety of the vehicle's occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel smell inside the vehicle
fuel gauge malfunction
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling
decreased fuel efficiency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power window system can cause inconvenience, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents due to obstructed visibility.
symptoms: The power window does not roll up or down
the power window rolls up or down intermittently
the power window is stuck in the open or closed position
the power window makes a strange noise while operating
the power window switch is unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to properly restrain the driver during a collision can lead to serious injuries, including head trauma, lacerations, and potentially even fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to hold the driver in place during a collision
allowing the driver's head to make contact with the windshield or other objects
resulting in injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Fading and Excessive Pedal Travel
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake fading and excessive pedal travel can lead to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and reduced vehicle control, potentially resulting in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels excessively before engaging
brakes feel like they're not functioning properly
brakes overheat
brake fade occurs during normal driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly diagnose brake system issues can lead to continued operation of a vehicle with compromised brakes, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Dealer or mechanic fails to identify brake system problems
brake system issues are misdiagnosed
brake system repairs are ineffective or incomplete.
